CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION secondMinimum(n  
                            edges  
                            time  
                            change)  
        SET web TO empty dictionary  
        SET index TO 1  
        WHILE index LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO n  
            SET web[index] TO empty list  
            INCREMENT index BY 1  
        END WHILE  
        
        SET pairIndex TO 0  
        WHILE pairIndex LESS THAN LENGTH(edges)  
            SET x TO edges[pairIndex][0]  
            SET y TO edges[pairIndex][1]  
            APPEND y TO web[x]  
            APPEND x TO web[y]  
            INCREMENT pairIndex BY 1  
        END WHILE  
        
        SET deq TO a list containing one tuple: (1, 0, 0)  
        SET minimalTimes TO a dictionary  
        SET keyIndex TO 1  
        WHILE keyIndex LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO n  
            SET minimalTimes[keyIndex] TO [∞, ∞]  
            INCREMENT keyIndex BY 1  
        END WHILE  
        SET minimalTimes[1][0] TO 0  
        
        WHILE LENGTH(deq) GREATER THAN 0  
            REMOVE first element FROM deq AND ASSIGN TO node, elapsed, cnt  
            
            IF node EQUALS n THEN  
                IF cnt EQUALS 1 THEN  
                    RETURN elapsed  
                ELSE  
                    CONTINUE  
                END IF  
            END IF  
            
            SET period TO elapsed DIV change  
            IF (period MOD 2) EQUALS 0 THEN  
                SET nxtElapsed TO elapsed PLUS time  
            ELSE  
                SET nxtElapsed TO ((period PLUS 1) MULTIPLIED BY change) PLUS time  
            END IF  
            
            SET nbIndex TO 0  
            SET neighborsList TO web[node]  
            WHILE nbIndex LESS THAN LENGTH(neighborsList)  
                SET neighbor TO neighborsList[nbIndex]  
                
                SET firstMin TO minimalTimes[neighbor][0]  
                SET secondMin TO minimalTimes[neighbor][1]  
                
                IF firstMin GREATER THAN nxtElapsed THEN  
                    SET minimalTimes[neighbor][1] TO firstMin  
                    SET minimalTimes[neighbor][0] TO nxtElapsed  
                    APPEND (neighbor, nxtElapsed, 0) TO deq  
                ELSE IF firstMin LESS THAN nxtElapsed AND nxtElapsed LESS THAN secondMin THEN  
                    SET minimalTimes[neighbor][1] TO nxtElapsed  
                    APPEND (neighbor, nxtElapsed, 1) TO deq  
                END IF  
                
                INCREMENT nbIndex BY 1  
            END WHILE  
        END WHILE  
        
        RETURN -1  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION secondMinimum(n  
                            edges  
                            time  
                            change)  
        SET graph TO list of empty lists for each integer from one TO n PLUS one  
        FOR each pair u AND v IN edges  
            APPEND v TO element at position u of graph  
            APPEND u TO element at position v of graph  
        END FOR  
          
        SET queue TO a double ended queue containing a tuple of one current vertex AND zero current time AND zero count  
        SET minTimes TO list containing two elements each set to infinite value for each integer from one TO n PLUS one  
        SET element at position one of minTimes at position zero TO zero  
          
        WHILE queue is not empty  
            REMOVE the first element FROM queue AND ASSIGN TO current AND currentTime AND count  
              
            IF current EQUALS n AND count EQUALS one  
                RETURN currentTime  
            END IF  
              
            IF integer division of currentTime BY change MODULO two EQUALS zero  
                SET nextTime TO currentTime PLUS time  
            ELSE  
                SET nextTime TO (integer division of currentTime BY change PLUS one) MULTIPLIED BY change PLUS time  
            END IF  
              
            FOR each neighbor IN element at position current of graph  
                IF element at position neighbor of minTimes at position zero GREATER THAN nextTime  
                    SET element at position neighbor of minTimes at position one TO element at position neighbor of minTimes at position zero  
                    SET element at position neighbor of minTimes at position zero TO nextTime  
                    APPEND tuple containing neighbor AND nextTime AND zero TO queue  
                ELSE IF element at position neighbor of minTimes at position zero LESS THAN nextTime AND nextTime LESS THAN element at position neighbor of minTimes at position one  
                    SET element at position neighbor of minTimes at position one TO nextTime  
                    APPEND tuple containing neighbor AND nextTime AND one TO queue  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END WHILE  
          
        RETURN negative one  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

        ASSIGN 0 TO accumulated

                LET rightDistance BE ABS(currentPos - startPos)
                LET leftDistance BE ABS(lowPos - startPos)
                LET gap BETWEEN BE currentPos - lowPos

                    BREAK OUT OF LOOP

                ASSIGN beginIndex + 1 TO beginIndex

            END IF

            ASSIGN endIndex + 1 TO endIndex
        END WHILE

        RETURN peakAmount
    END FUNCTION

CLASS Solution
    FUNCTION maximumGood(statements)
        LET count_humans BE 0
        LET total_people BE LENGTH(statements)
        
        FUNCTION evaluate(index, state_map)
            IF index IS total_people THEN
                LET truth_map BE EMPTY MAP
                FOR pos IN 0 TO total_people - 1 BY 1
                    IF ((state_map >> pos) AND 1) = 1 THEN
                        SET truth_map[pos] = TRUE
                    ELSE
                        SET truth_map[pos] = FALSE
                    END IF
                END FOR
                FOR examine IN 0 TO total_people - 1 BY 1
                    IF truth_map[examine] = TRUE THEN
                        FOR target IN 0 TO total_people - 1 BY 1
                            LET claim = statements[examine][target]
                            IF claim = 0 AND truth_map[target] = TRUE THEN
                                RETURN FALSE
                            ELSE IF claim = 1 AND truth_map[target] = FALSE THEN
                                RETURN FALSE
                            END IF
                        END FOR
                    END IF
                END FOR
                RETURN TRUE
            END IF
            RETURN evaluate(index + 1, state_map) OR evaluate(index + 1, state_map OR (1 << index))
        END FUNCTION
        
        FUNCTION count_set_bits(number)
            LET bits_count BE 0
            WHILE number > 0
                bits_count = bits_count + (number AND 1)
                number = number >> 1
            END WHILE
            RETURN bits_count
        END FUNCTION
        
        FOR mask FROM 0 TO (2 ^ total_people) - 1 BY 1
            IF evaluate(0, mask) = TRUE THEN
                LET current_count BE count_set_bits(mask)
                IF current_count > count_humans THEN
                    count_humans = current_count
                END IF
            END IF
        END FOR
        
        RETURN count_humans
    END FUNCTION
END CLASS

	TYPE gcdMap IS map FROM int TO int

			IF idx EQUALS length(nums) THEN RETURN END IF  
			SET currNum TO nums[idx]  
			SET currGcd TO gcd(currNum, k)  
			IF NOT frequency HAS currGcd THEN frequency[currGcd] = 0 END IF  
			frequency[currGcd] = frequency[currGcd] + 1  
			computeGcdCount(idx + 1)  
		END FUNCTION

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION countPairs(nums k)  
        SET gcd_count TO a new counter collection  
        
        FOR each num IN nums  
            INCREMENT the count in gcd_count for the gcd of num AND k BY one  
        END FOR  
        
        SET total_pairs TO zero  
        
        SET gcd_values TO the list of keys of gcd_count  
        SET n TO the length of gcd_values  
        
        FOR i FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
            FOR j FROM i TO n MINUS one  
                SET gcd1 TO the element at position i of gcd_values  
                SET gcd2 TO the element at position j of gcd_values  
                
                IF the remainder of gcd1 MULTIPLIED BY gcd2 DIVIDED BY k EQUALS zero THEN  
                    IF i EQUALS j THEN  
                        INCREMENT total_pairs BY the count of gcd1 in gcd_count MULTIPLIED BY the count of gcd1 in gcd_count MINUS one DIVIDED BY two  
                    ELSE  
                        INCREMENT total_pairs BY the count of gcd1 in gcd_count MULTIPLIED BY the count of gcd2 in gcd_count  
                    END IF  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        
        RETURN total_pairs  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution
    FUNCTION minimumFinishTime(tires, changeTime, numLaps)
        INITIALIZE aggregate_min WITH a queue CONTAINING positive_infinity REPEATED 15 times
        
        FUNCTION explore_laps(tire_idx)
            IF tire_idx >= LENGTH(tires)
                RETURN
            END IF

            LET base_time, factor BE tires[tire_idx]
            LET acc_time BE 0

            FUNCTION lap_recursion(step)
                IF step > 14
                    RETURN
                END IF
                
                LET lap_duration BE base_time * (factor ^ step)
                IF lap_duration > changeTime + base_time
                    RETURN
                END IF
                
                acc_time = acc_time + lap_duration
                IF acc_time < aggregate_min[step]
                    aggregate_min[step] = acc_time
                END IF
                
                lap_recursion(step + 1)
            END FUNCTION

            lap_recursion(0)
            explore_laps(tire_idx + 1)
        END FUNCTION

        CALL explore_laps(0)

        INITIALIZE dp_array WITH a list of length (numLaps + 1) FILLED WITH positive_infinity
        dp_array[0] = 0

        FUNCTION fill_dp(current_lap)
            IF current_lap > numLaps
                RETURN
            END IF
            
            FUNCTION try_segments(segment)
                IF segment > MIN(current_lap - 1, 14)
                    fill_dp(current_lap + 1)
                    RETURN
                END IF
                
                LET trial_time BE dp_array[current_lap - segment - 1] + aggregate_min[segment] + changeTime
                IF trial_time < dp_array[current_lap]
                    dp_array[current_lap] = trial_time
                END IF
                
                try_segments(segment + 1)
            END FUNCTION
            
            try_segments(0)
        END FUNCTION
        
        fill_dp(1)
        RETURN dp_array[numLaps] - changeTime
    END FUNCTION
END CLASS

CLASS Solution
    FUNCTION minimumFinishTime(tires, changeTime, numLaps)
        SET min_times TO a list of length FIFTEEN with all elements set to positive infinity
        FOR each pair of first_variable AND ratio IN tires
            SET total_time TO zero
            FOR index FROM zero TO FOURTEEN
                SET lap_time TO first_variable MULTIPLIED BY ratio RAISED TO the power of index
                IF lap_time IS GREATER THAN changeTime PLUS first_variable
                    BREAK the current loop
                END IF
                SET total_time TO total_time PLUS lap_time
                IF total_time IS LESS THAN element at position index of min_times
                    SET element at position index of min_times TO total_time
                END IF
            END FOR
        END FOR

        SET dp TO a list of length numLaps PLUS one with all elements set to positive infinity
        SET element at position zero of dp TO zero

        FOR i FROM one TO numLaps
            FOR j FROM zero TO THE LESSER OF i MINUS one AND FOURTEEN
                SET candidate_time TO element at position i MINUS j MINUS one of dp PLUS element at position j of min_times PLUS changeTime
                IF candidate_time IS LESS THAN element at position i of dp
                    SET element at position i of dp TO candidate_time
                END IF
            END FOR
        END FOR

        RETURN element at position numLaps of dp MINUS changeTime
    END FUNCTION

            SET interval_end TO the end value at position one of the element at position i of intervals

            SET longest TO the greatest value among the differences between end and start values PLUS one for each tuple in intervals

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION maximumBeauty(flowers AS list OF integer newFlowers AS integer target AS integer full AS integer partial) AS integer  
        SORT the flowers list in ascending order  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF flowers  
        SET max_beauty TO zero  
          
        SET prefix_sum TO a list of zeros with LENGTH n PLUS one  
        FOR i FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
            SET element at position i PLUS one of prefix_sum TO element at position i of prefix_sum PLUS element at position i of flowers  
        END FOR  
          
        SET complete_gardens TO zero  
        FOR i FROM n MINUS one DOWN TO zero  
            IF element at position i of flowers GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO target  
                INCREMENT complete_gardens BY one  
            ELSE  
                BREAK the loop  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
          
        SET remaining_flowers TO newFlowers  
        SET max_incomplete_flowers TO zero  
          
        FOR i FROM complete_gardens TO n  
            IF i GREATER THAN zero  
                SET needed_flowers TO target MINUS element at position n MINUS i of flowers  
                DECREMENT remaining_flowers BY needed_flowers  
                IF remaining_flowers LESS THAN zero  
                    BREAK the loop  
                END IF  
            END IF  
              
            SET left TO zero  
            SET right TO n MINUS i MINUS one  
            WHILE left LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO right  
                SET mid TO the INTEGER DIVISION OF left PLUS right BY two  
                SET cost TO element at position mid of flowers MULTIPLIED BY mid PLUS one MINUS element at position mid PLUS one of prefix_sum  
                IF cost GREATER THAN remaining_flowers  
                    DECREMENT right BY one SET TO mid MINUS one  
                ELSE  
                    INCREMENT left BY one SET TO mid PLUS one  
                END IF  
            END WHILE  
              
            IF right GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO zero  
                SET current_max_incomplete TO element at position right of flowers PLUS  
                    DIVIDE remaining_flowers MINUS (element at position right of flowers MULTIPLIED BY right PLUS one MINUS element at position right PLUS one of prefix_sum) BY right PLUS one  
                SET max_incomplete_flowers TO current_max_incomplete  
            ELSE  
                SET max_incomplete_flowers TO zero  
            END IF  
              
            SET total_beauty TO i MULTIPLIED BY full PLUS  
                MINIMUM OF max_incomplete_flowers AND target MINUS one MULTIPLIED BY partial  
            IF total_beauty GREATER THAN max_beauty  
                SET max_beauty TO total_beauty  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
          
        RETURN max_beauty  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION maximumScore(scores, edges)  
        CREATE graph AS an empty mapping with default empty array  
        SET index_u TO 0  
        WHILE index_u < LENGTH(edges)  
            SET node_u TO edges[index_u][0]  
            SET node_v TO edges[index_u][1]  
            INSERT [scores[node_v], node_v] INTO graph[node_u] AT END  
            INSERT [scores[node_u], node_u] INTO graph[node_v] AT END  
            SET index_u TO index_u + 1  
        END WHILE  
        FOR each node IN KEYS(graph)  
            SET connected_nodes TO graph[node]  
            SORT connected_nodes DESCENDING BY first element of each pair  
            SET graph[node] TO SLICE connected_nodes FROM 0 TO 2  
        END FOR  
        SET max_score TO -1  
        SET idx_edge TO 0  
        WHILE idx_edge < LENGTH(edges)  
            SET edge_u TO edges[idx_edge][0]  
            SET edge_v TO edges[idx_edge][1]  
            SET u_pairs TO graph[edge_u]  
            SET v_pairs TO graph[edge_v]  
            SET ind_x TO 0

                SET x_node TO u_pairs[ind_x][1]

                    END IF  
                    SET ind_y TO ind_y + 1  
                END WHILE  
                SET ind_x TO ind_x + 1  
            END WHILE  
            SET idx_edge TO idx_edge + 1  
        END WHILE  
        RETURN max_score  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION maximumCost(n, highways, k)  
        CREATE adjacency_list AS a map with default empty list  
        FOR route IN highways  
            LET a = route[0]  
            LET b = route[1]  
            LET fee = route[2]  
            APPEND (b, fee) TO adjacency_list[a]  
            APPEND (a, fee) TO adjacency_list[b]  
        END FOR  

        SET best_value TO negative infinity  

        FUNCTION dfs(current_city, visited_nodes, current_sum, edges_count)  
            IF edges_count IS k THEN  
                IF current_sum > best_value THEN  
                    best_value = current_sum  
                END IF  
                RETURN  
            END IF  

            FOR EACH (next_city, toll_cost) IN adjacency_list[current_city]  
                IF next_city NOT IN visited_nodes THEN  
                    visited_nodes.ADD(next_city)  
                    CALL dfs(next_city, visited_nodes, current_sum + toll_cost, edges_count + 1)  
                    visited_nodes.REMOVE(next_city)  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FUNCTION  

        FOR city_index FROM 0 TO n - 1 DO  
            SET visited_nodes TO new set containing city_index  
            CALL dfs(city_index, visited_nodes, 0, 0)  
        END FOR  

        RETURN best_value  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution
    FUNCTION appealSum(s)
        ASSIGN last TO a dictionary with keys from 0 to 25 each paired with value -1
        ASSIGN agg TO 0
        ASSIGN acc TO 0

        ASSIGN keys TO list of integers from 0 up to (length of s minus 1)

        FUNCTION recurse(pos_list)
            IF pos_list IS EMPTY THEN
                RETURN
            ELSE
                ASSIGN curr_pos TO pos_list[0]
                ASSIGN rem TO sublist of pos_list from index 1 onward

                ASSIGN ch TO s[curr_pos]
                ASSIGN idx TO numeric code of ch MINUS numeric code of 'a'

                ASSIGN diff TO curr_pos MINUS last[idx]
                ASSIGN acc TO acc PLUS diff
                ASSIGN agg TO agg PLUS acc
                ASSIGN last[idx] TO curr_pos

                recurse(rem)
            END IF
        END FUNCTION

        CALL recurse(keys)

        RETURN agg
    END FUNCTION
END CLASS

        SET row_count TO the LENGTH OF grid

    FUNCTION areSentencesSimilarTwo(sentence1 sentence1 TO sentence1 OF TYPE list OF strings sentence2 sentence2 TO sentence2 OF TYPE list OF strings similarPairs similarPairs TO similarPairs OF TYPE list OF list OF strings) RETURNS boolean

    END FUNCTION
